</taxonomicName>
holotype, skeleton. Scanning electron micrographs. (A) Calycocome. (B) Atrial hexactin. (C) Pappocome-like oxyhexaster with most secondary rays broken off. (D) Regular oxyhexaster. (E) Discaster.
